actions.in_committee: House Committee on Ways and Means

official_title: To repeal the nondiscrimination rules of section 89 of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 and restore prior law.

summary.text: Repeals provisions of the Tax Reform Act of 1986 that establish nondiscrimination requirements for coverage and benefits under certain statutory employee benefit plans. (The consequence is the repeal of section 89 of the Internal Revenue Code.)

titles.title: To repeal the nondiscrimination rules of section 89 of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 and restore prior law.
